
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a double forward slash "//" with a single forward slash "/" in a concatenated string. The [strings.concat] slot is used to create the initial string, and the [strings.replace] slot performs the replacement operation. The result is a modified string with all instances of "//" replaced by "/". 
 * 
 * 1. [strings.replace] - Initiates the string replacement operation.
 * 2. [x:@strings.concat] - Specifies the target string for the replacement operation, which is the result of a concatenation.
 * 3. [.:] - The first child node of [strings.replace] specifies the substring to be replaced, in this case, "//".
 * 4. [.:] - The second child node of [strings.replace] specifies the replacement substring, in this case, "/".
 */
strings.replace:x:@strings.concat
   .://
   .:/
